Actually, creating a Field with a Reader means the field data is=20
"unstored".  It is indexed, but the original text is not retrievable as=20=

it is not in the index (yes, it is tokenized, but not kept as a unit,=20
and is very unlikely to be the same as the original text)

If you need the text to be stored in the index, read the text into a=20
String and use that Field.Text variant rather than a Reader.

	Erik


On Jan 5, 2004, at 11:35 AM, Grant Ingersoll wrote:

> I believe since you created the field using a Reader, you have to use=20=

> the Field.readerValue() method instead of the stringValue() method and=20=

> then handle the reader appropriately.  I don't know if there is anyway=20=

> to determine which one is used for a given field other than to test=20
> for null on the readerValue()?????
>
> -Grant
