>>> "Erik Hatcher" <erik@ehatchersolutions.com> 01/08/04 01:43PM >>>
On Jan 7, 2004, at 3:54 PM, Jim Hargrave wrote:
> Looks like I will have to implement my own PhraseQuery that uses a=20
> standard string edit distance measure. What is the easiest way to do=20
> this? Should I override PhraseQuery - then override the=20
> SloppyPhraseScorer? I have my own query parser so I can make any=20
> adjustments needed when building aquery.

Probably best to keep this on the lucene-user e-mail list, but it is=20
non-trivial to implement a custom Query.   While PhraseQuery itself can=20
be extended, there are several pieces it uses which are currently=20
scoped at package visibility level only.

Even if you are using the built-in QueryParser, you can override the=20
method that constructs the PhraseQuery.

