I just aborted a re-indexing operation (because it was taking too much =
time - will run it overnight instead).  But I was surprised by what I =
found in the index directory, which contained a total of 1,402 index =
files!  It started out with 36 files with the name of "_I9a.*", followed =
by groups of 72 files with names like "_17si.*" and so forth.

Is this normal?

Also, I noticed that during the indexing it would chug along, indexing =
at a pretty decent rate, and then, every so often (I would estimate =
every several hundred added files) it would stop for perhaps 10 - 30 =
seconds (occasionally longer), doing a bunch of disk activity.  Then it =
would resume again - almost like it was optimizing.  (I'm doing this on =
a notebook, so the disk IO is probably fairly slow.)

Is this normal?

Regards,

Terry

PS: The code I'm using to do the indexing is below:

import npg1.search.WebExecAnalyzer;
import org.apache.lucene.index.IndexWriter;
import npg1.search.WESimilarity2;
import npg1.search.WPDocument2a;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.Date;

class IndexWPFiles2a {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
=20
 //args[0] =3D location of target directory to be indexed
 //args[1] =3D location of index directory (in which to create index =
files)
=20
 System.out.println("starting");=20
 try {
  Date start =3D new Date();
 =20
  String target =3D "c:/master_db/master_xml";
  if(args[0] !=3D null) {
   target =3D args[0];
  } =20
  String index =3D "c:/master_db/master_index";
  if(args[1] !=3D null) {
   index =3D args[1];
  }
       =20
  IndexWriter writer =3D null;
  if(args.length < 3) {
   writer =3D new IndexWriter(index, new WebExecAnalyzer(), true);
   writer.mergeFactor =3D 50;
   writer.setSimilarity(new WESimilarity2());
   indexDocs(writer, new File(target));
  } else {
   writer =3D new IndexWriter(index, new WebExecAnalyzer(), false);
   writer.setSimilarity(new WESimilarity2());
  }
  writer.optimize();
  writer.close();
 =20
  Date end =3D new Date();
 =20
  System.out.print(end.getTime() - start.getTime());
  System.out.println(" total milliseconds");
=20
 } catch (Exception e) {
  System.out.println(" caught a " + e.getClass() +
    "\n with message: " + e.getMessage());
 }
  }

  public static void indexDocs(IndexWriter writer, File file)
       throws Exception {
 //System.out.println("starting indexing with internal path");=20
 if (file.isDirectory()) {
  String[] files =3D file.list();
  for (int i =3D 0; i < files.length; i++){
   //System.out.println("recursive call");
   indexDocs(writer, new File(file, files[i]));
  }
 } else {
  try {
   System.out.println("adding " + file);
   writer.addDocument(WPDocument2a.Document(file));
  } catch (Exception e) {
   System.out.println("error adding "+file+" -  Exception: =
"+e.getMessage());
  }
 }
  }
}

