there are just about as many ways of doing it as there are papers that =
talk about automatic relevance feedback. many require domain-specific =
reference documents that are full of facts and therefore good sources of =
related words. some people use Wordnet. some of these techniques can add =
400-500 terms into a query if they are searching long documents and =
using reference documents that are equally long. the technique is very =
important only when searching long documents and almost irrelevant for =
very short ones.

