The source code of the method.=20
It fails at ( writer.optimize();// This is where it fails), which is not =

within a try/catch.=20
It works great with the lucene-1.2 version but fails with the=20
lucene-1.3-final.jar=20
Any ideas would be appreciated.=20
Apologies for posting this question to the dev list initially.=20

---- code ----=20
public synchronized void index() throws Exception {=20
final ProductDocumentBuilder productDocument =3D=20
ProductDocumentBuilder.getInstance();=20
productFactory =3D new ProductFactory(productHome, pgroupHome);=20

registerDocumentBuilder( "ml.product ", productDocument);=20
registerFactory( "ml.product ", productFactory);=20

logger.info( "index() starting. ");=20

logger.info( " loaded data, indexing ");=20

// create the indexer=20
IndexWriter writer =3D new IndexWriter(workDir, new=20
StandardAnalyzer(), true);=20
writer.mergeFactor =3D mergeFactor;=20
long start =3D System.currentTimeMillis();=20
// pass in a dummy new Object=20
Iterator allProducts =3D productFactory.contentIterate(new Object());=20
int i =3D 0;=20
while (allProducts.hasNext()) {=20
i++;=20
SearchProduct product =3D (SearchProduct) allProducts.next();=20
try {=20
writer.addDocument(productDocument.getDocument(product));=20
} catch (Exception e) {=20
logger.warn( "Failed to index Product: " + product.getPK(),=20
e);=20
}=20
}=20

writer.optimize();// This is where it fails=20
writer.close();=20
logger.info( " indexer took " + (System.currentTimeMillis() -=20
start) + " milliseconds. To index " + i + " products ");=20
productFactory.flush();=20
}=20
-- end code -------------------=20

- thank you,=20
